1
00:01:44,630 --> 00:01:52,630
=Lucky's First Love=

2
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:55,720
=Episode 4=

3
00:01:57,550 --> 00:01:59,950
But, aren't you curious to know

4
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:02,480
where I stayed the night?

5
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:04,670
It couldn't have happened if your boss
hadn't asked you to work overtime,

6
00:02:04,670 --> 00:02:06,550
and your family were not at home.

7
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:08,720
In that case, he couldn't have left you alone, right?

8
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,000
You're right.

9
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:15,110
But, he's a guy.

10
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,470
I planned to tell you about it,

11
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:21,030
but I was afraid I couldn't make it clear by phone.

12
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,520
And it was very late,

13
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,630
so, I had to stay over at his home.

14
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:24,320
But nothing happened

15
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,160
between me and him.

16
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:26,880
Are you afraid I'd get the wrong idea?

17
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:32,360
Isn't it usually the case?

18
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,720
Don't worry. I won't get you wrong.

19
00:02:35,030 --> 00:02:36,910
If you had an affair with your boss,

20
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,000
you couldn't have gone on a blind date.

21
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,000
Sounds reasonable.

22
00:02:41,830 --> 00:02:45,030
Chu Nan, thank you for trusting me.

23
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,320
Well. It's getting late.

24
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,550
I'll leave you be.

25
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:51,160
Let me see you off.

26
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:51,720
Don't bother.

27
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,360
You're injured. How can I let you do that?

28
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,720
Your father would scold me if he sees it.

29
00:02:57,630 --> 00:02:58,800
Drive safely!

30
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:02,800
Bye.

31
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:21,630
Pick it up.

32
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:24,550
Mr. Xia, why are you still there?

33
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:25,800
I'm waiting for you to finish your work.

34
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,190
I'm sorry

35
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,160
to keep you waiting for two hours.

36
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,520
Don't you feel bored?

37
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:32,390
No. I don't.

38
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:34,000
I had dinner.

39
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,630
And I listened to the stupid conversation

40
00:03:35,630 --> 00:03:37,000
between you and your boyfriend.

41
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:38,600
What?

42
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:41,960
How can you eavesdrop on me?

43
00:03:43,110 --> 00:03:44,190
The other day,

44
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:45,520
you gossiped about my private life

45
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,960
in the WeChat group.

46
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:51,320
So, you took your revenge, right?

47
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,470
But I didn't expect

48
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,550
he has so much confidence in you.

49
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:57,080
What do you mean?

50
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,160
It turns out he thinks

51
00:03:59,270 --> 00:04:01,160
no men would have interest in you wherever you go.

52
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:08,030
Mr. Xia, I know it's hard for you to understand,

53
00:04:08,270 --> 00:04:09,880
but that's what it's like for adults.

54
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,790
We have our own space

55
00:04:11,950 --> 00:04:13,270
and also have much confidence in each other.

56
00:04:13,510 --> 00:04:14,880
It's called mature love.

57
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:16,160
No offense,

58
00:04:16,350 --> 00:04:18,320
but if you had learned from my boyfriend,

59
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:19,480
Shen Qing

60
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,200
couldn't have misunderstood us.

61
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,160
Learn from him?

62
00:04:23,350 --> 00:04:25,040
I'm not as stupid as you.

63
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:26,600
Anyway, I don't have an obligation

64
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,880
to explain my private life to you.

65
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,670
Take your time and think it over.

66
00:04:30,110 --> 00:04:31,880
I'll email you when I get the plan done.

67
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:32,270
Bye.

68
00:04:35,270 --> 00:04:35,670
If you hang me up…

69
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,320
I'm bound to deduct a large amount
from your year-end bonus.

70
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,270
It takes a long time for a bone to heal properly.

71
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,480
You should take a few more days off.

72
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,440
Why are you anxious to come to the office?

73
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:14,510
It's okay.

74
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,440
I've stayed at home for several days.

75
00:05:16,510 --> 00:05:17,600
I'm quite satisfied.

76
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,350
I'd rather come to the office

77
00:05:19,350 --> 00:05:20,270
than stay at home

78
00:05:20,270 --> 00:05:21,510
and talk to my boss on WeChat.

79
00:05:22,670 --> 00:05:23,920
He really cares about you.

80
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:25,950
I hope I can see him someday.

81
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,070
He's short-tempered,

82
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:30,200
but he always strives for perfection
as for his work.

83
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:32,270
I can learn a lot from him in this aspect.

84
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,790
I just wish

85
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:35,160
he could stop monitoring us.

86
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:35,950
Get on.

87
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,270
Do you want to have some cake?

88
00:05:57,270 --> 00:05:58,510
Shall we pull off and get some?

89
00:05:59,670 --> 00:05:59,920
No.

90
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:08,200
Is it because you think it's embarrassing

91
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,390
to admit you like to eat cake?

92
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:18,320
Miss Shen, are you going out?

93
00:06:18,670 --> 00:06:19,510
Mr. Li.

94
00:06:19,790 --> 00:06:20,950
Nina's Dad.

95
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,390
You know him, too.

96
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,200
He often came to my mom recently.

97
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:26,000
He also said he wants to be my dad.

98
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:49,000
Chu Nan, I think we've got the wrong way.

99
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:57,920
Chu Nan, what's wrong?

100
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,160
Chu Nan, sorry.

101
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:25,110
Xing Yun.

102
00:07:27,790 --> 00:07:28,920
Let's get married.

103
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:32,200
Huh?

104
00:07:54,510 --> 00:07:57,000
I suddenly proposed to you just now.

105
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,670
You must be scared, right?

106
00:08:02,510 --> 00:08:03,880
Can you ask your mom

107
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:05,670
for the invoice when you go back?

108
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:07,920
I'll pay for it.

109
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,270
Are you refusing my proposal?

110
00:08:11,510 --> 00:08:11,920
No.

111
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,110
Yes.

112
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:16,440
No. I mean

113
00:08:16,790 --> 00:08:18,550
I've never thought about getting married

114
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,110
now that we just got to know
each other a month ago.

115
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:22,670
I think the bracelet must be expensive.

116
00:08:23,350 --> 00:08:24,760
If I can't pay it off,

117
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,320
I can pay by monthly installments.

118
00:08:28,590 --> 00:08:31,200
I can also write you an IOU.

119
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,760
Even if you don't want to marry me,

120
00:08:32,790 --> 00:08:34,080
you don't have to consider me

121
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,590
a penny pincher.

122
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:37,840
I didn't mean it.

123
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,640
Alright. I see.

124
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,080
It's me that should say sorry.

125
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:45,670
I've been under pressure recently.

126
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:51,400
Just forget about the proposal.

127
00:08:53,350 --> 00:08:54,350
Are you okay?

128
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,150
Is it about your work?

129
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,320
Go home. Don't let your parents worry about you.

130
00:09:06,790 --> 00:09:09,030
Drive safely.

131
00:09:35,230 --> 00:09:36,280
I really don't know

132
00:09:38,470 --> 00:09:39,280
what I'm doing.

133
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,320
Chu Nan proposed to you!

134
00:09:43,910 --> 00:09:45,280
What a perfect matchmaker I am!

135
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,640
I can't help admiring myself.

136
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:48,000
Show me the diamond ring.

137
00:09:48,470 --> 00:09:49,670
There is no ring.

138
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,110
Don't try to lie to me.

139
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,670
Chu Nan is generous.

140
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:55,350
Tell me. When are you getting married?

141
00:09:55,670 --> 00:09:56,640
Where will you hold the wedding ceremony?

142
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,440
This wedding dress is great.

143
00:09:58,550 --> 00:09:59,350
You can try it on.

144
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,000
No way. I have to ask him about it.

145
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:04,590
Stop it.

146
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:06,110
I didn't say yes.

147
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:09,150
Yun, you have to plan for yourself.

148
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:11,470
Life is short.

149
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:13,790
I'm telling you.

150
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,550
Never listen to those celibates.

151
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:19,030
What they say about freedom
or vagabondage is all nonsense.

152
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:22,200
Women are born to be animals who like to nest.

153
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:24,910
A marriage is like a nest.

154
00:10:25,350 --> 00:10:26,880
When you get married,

155
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,470
you'll have someone to rely on

156
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:29,880
and feel safe.

157
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,030
Look at me.

158
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,470
I'm getting into a new nest

159
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:36,640
soon after I got out of an old one.

160
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,520
You know, Chu Nan is…

161
00:10:41,590 --> 00:10:43,520
Here is how the project related
to “Infinite Unknown Love”

162
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:44,840
is progressing.

163
00:10:45,110 --> 00:10:47,110
We've also prepared promotion plans

164
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:48,520
and the quarterly financial statements.

165
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:50,590
Please let us know
if there is anything we can improve.

166
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:52,670
As for the project,

167
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,880
I've heard the person-in-charge

168
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,350
has no experience of planning at all.

169
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:59,080
Don't you think it's too risky?

170
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:00,150
I trust her.

171
00:11:00,590 --> 00:11:02,230
Mr. Xia, we've checked

172
00:11:02,230 --> 00:11:03,550
that girl's background.

173
00:11:03,590 --> 00:11:05,200
I don't think she has any special talent.

174
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,790
She graduated from a common university

175
00:11:07,550 --> 00:11:08,840
and her previous work

176
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:10,880
has nothing to do with planning.

177
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,790
If you don't like the current planner,

178
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:13,840
we can hire a new one

179
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,520
even if we may have to pay more.

180
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:17,000
How about someone who has studied abroad?

181
00:11:17,230 --> 00:11:19,110
For TIG, what's most important
is not qualifications,

182
00:11:19,550 --> 00:11:20,280
but capacity.

183
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:24,350
Lots of people finish their work
by using others' experience for reference

184
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:26,760
and even copying,

185
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:29,590
but we need those
who are enthusiastic about their job

186
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,350
and can think creatively.

187
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,280
Come out. Let me have a look.

188
00:11:38,590 --> 00:11:40,200
I think you'll steal the show

189
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:41,400
if you're my bridesmaid.

190
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,590
Really?

191
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,000
I'm leaving.

192
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:45,880
I'm absent from work to keep you company.

193
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:48,910
Come on. You'll be my bridesmaid
no matter what. Okay?

194
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:50,030
Pass me your cell phone.

195
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:51,150
For what?

196
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:52,840
To take a picture of you.

197
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,760
You look so nice in it.

198
00:11:56,670 --> 00:11:59,030
Perfect. I'll send it to Chu Nan.

199
00:12:01,150 --> 00:12:02,110
Miss, do me a favor.

200
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:03,640
Don't. Give it back.

201
00:12:03,710 --> 00:12:03,960
Hold on.

202
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:04,520
Stop it.

203
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:08,000
Chu Nan, come marry me!

204
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:08,760
Xing Cheng!

205
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:09,590
I can't give it back now.

206
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:11,150
What if you withdraw it?

207
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,150
Withdraw it!

208
00:12:12,230 --> 00:12:13,030
Miss, take it away.

209
00:12:13,110 --> 00:12:13,910
Hurry up. Take it away.

210
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:14,960
Give it back to me.

211
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,910
I'll give it back to you soon!

212
00:12:17,350 --> 00:12:18,670
Just after the shooting.

213
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,280
You bully me.

214
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:24,590
Speed is everything

215
00:12:25,110 --> 00:12:26,200
in the market.

216
00:12:26,590 --> 00:12:27,280
Nobody cares about how you do it.

217
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:29,470
For game developers, every minute counts.

218
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:30,610
You're gambling.

219
00:12:30,610 --> 00:12:31,110
(Xing Yun: Come marry me)
You're gambling.

220
00:12:31,110 --> 00:12:31,400
(Xing Yun: Come marry me)

221
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,010
(Xing Yun: Come marry me)
What if she screws it up?

222
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:32,710
What if she screws it up?

223
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:38,640
Xia Ke.

224
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:42,110
Mr. Sun,

225
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:44,880
as far as I know,

226
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,280
besides “Infinite Unknown Love”,

227
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:49,280
you also invested in three other games.

228
00:12:52,470 --> 00:12:52,760
That's right.

229
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:55,320
Their production cycles and update rates

230
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:56,400
are better than ours,

231
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,400
but we're the only one that makes profits.

232
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:00,960
Am I right?

233
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:04,110
Uh.

234
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,550
To improve the efficiency,

235
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,440
I'm going back now to supervise
and urge the person-in-charge.

236
00:13:12,030 --> 00:13:13,910
We're pressed for time. I'm leaving.

237
00:13:15,710 --> 00:13:16,550
How can he…

238
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,520
He's too arrogant.

239
00:13:21,710 --> 00:13:23,280
Mr. Sun, calm down.

240
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:29,550
Why haven't you been back?

241
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,280
I spent too much time on shooting.

242
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,520
I even missed my lunch.

243
00:13:32,710 --> 00:13:33,910
I'll be back after having some noodles.

244
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,960
Hurry up.

245
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,110
Amy just called and said

246
00:13:37,110 --> 00:13:38,670
she and Xia Ke are on the way back.

247
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:42,640
Isn't he having a meeting with investors?

248
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,550
Why is he back so soon?

249
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,640
Did he offend investors again?

250
00:13:48,030 --> 00:13:49,200
You know me so well.

251
00:13:54,350 --> 00:13:55,590
Mr. Xia.

252
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,760
I know the lunch break is over.

253
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:00,880
I'm going back now.

254
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:03,960
Where did you go in the morning?

255
00:14:05,790 --> 00:14:06,400
Um.

256
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,670
I went out for inspiration.

257
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,960
You don't like that restaurant, right?

258
00:14:14,350 --> 00:14:16,000
So, I went out to seek inspiration.

259
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,670
I'm going back.

260
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:21,400
Come back.

261
00:14:27,550 --> 00:14:28,280
Finish your noodles.

262
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:31,110
Oh.

263
00:14:43,590 --> 00:14:44,710
Do you know

264
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,320
what's the most sensitive subject
in a relationship?

265
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,200
Of course it's break-up.

266
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:52,840
It's marriage.

267
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:56,000
Why?

268
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,910
Isn't marriage the happy ending everyone wants?

269
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:01,470
It also means game over.

270
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:14,280
You were absent from work to take photos, right?

271
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,400
Uh. It's not me.

272
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:19,470
It's my cousin that took it.

273
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:21,470
Maybe it's because I put you
on the top of my contact list, so she…

274
00:15:26,470 --> 00:15:27,280
Mr. Xia, I'm sorry.

275
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,230
I shouldn't have skipped work

276
00:15:28,230 --> 00:15:29,910
to keep my cousin company.

277
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,230
Are you so eager to get married?

278
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:38,000
Let's get married.

279
00:15:40,710 --> 00:15:41,440
No. No!

280
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:42,760
I didn't say yes. Really.

281
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:52,200
